subanswer.text: There are 4 dozens (each dozen contains 12) eggs from the cases, hence they make up 4 * 12 = 48 eggs, adding the other 2 loose ones results in an overall count of 48 + 2 = 50 eggs used. The answer is 50.

subanswer.text: With 50 eggs where every glass takes 5 eggs, you will get a perfect division resulting in exactly 50 / 5 = 10 full glasses. The answer is 10.
